I'm biased as hell when it comes to the "what drawing software is better" question cause I've been a diehard user of CSP since I first got a drawing tablet. so take this comparison with a massive grain of salt.
I feel that CSP has more quality of life services - such as the 3d poser engine, assets store, and full comic-making suite built-in. krita's price can't be beaten, and they've certainly have my first recommendation for free drawing software, but CSP just feels more "complete" to me. it can import PS brushes and files, and anything that can pull the rug out from under adobe has my support.
it's like... it's like Photoshop and GIMP. there's a reason why people use and like GIMP, but there's also a reason why photoshit is the fucking industry standard.
it's just more complete.

get CSP if you have the spare dosh, or if it's on sale. (don't get EX cause that's the animation suite) If you love your krita, support the devs with the money you'd spend on a copy of CSP.
